Head of Product Management


Company:Aegon  Asset  Management  
Location:IA
Date:06/02/2015

Company and Divisional Description:This  position  will  be  with  Aegon  Asset  Management  (AAM)  US.  AAM  is  a  leading  global  asset management organization with operating businesses in Continental Europe, the United States, and the United Kingdom. With a focus on excellence, trust, and partnership, the AAM companies manage assets for Aegon and Transamerica insurance and operating companies, as well as institutional and mutual fund clients around the globe. The AAM US companies are Aegon USA Investment Management, LLC (AUIM) and Aegon USA Realty Advisors, LLC (AURA). AUIM is an investment advisor registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission and specializes in management of fixed income and multi-asset class portfolios. AURA is an industry leader in real estate asset management and services, managing commercial real estate, commercial loans, and other real estate-related investments. Headquartered in Cedar  Rapids,  IA,  AUIM  and  AURA  have  employees  in  several  cities  from  Baltimore,  MD,  to  San Francisco, CA.This position may be considered in AAM locations of Baltimore, MD or Chicago, IL alternatively.Overview & Responsibilities:To provide strategic and tactical management of the product portfolio for the U.S. including all fixed income, real estate and asset allocation products. This requires extensive engagement with colleagues across the organization. The role is accountable for ensuring that the product range remains relevant, compliant and competitive, and is promoted to a consistently high standard, while interpreting market requirements and regulations.� 	Develop, manage and enhance the organization�s investment products and services.� 	Define competitive market requirements and opportunities to develop new investment products and services and provide ongoing support to ensure the competitiveness of existing products in liaison with colleagues in Real Estate, Product and Marketing, Investment Management, Client Solutions and Distribution.� 	Identify, agree and prioritize product amendments and enhancements to ensure products areand remain relevant, compliant and competitive.� 	Originate and test investment concepts, prioritizing resource utilization and predicting and modeling results.� 	Chair or support the relevant product committee(s) to present ideas, gain their buy-in andapproval, and provide current views of market trends.� 	Lead and develop the Product team to achieve and maintain a high level of technical and analytical expertise across the product range.� 	Work collaboratively across the organization to ensure successful implementation of new products and services and changes to existing products and services. � 	Responsible for compliance of the product portfolio with relevant external regulations and internal policies including but not limited to the Product Approval and Management Policy and Aegon Market Conduct Principles.� 	Develop department mission and sets stretch goals and objectives for product staff aligned withoverall company goals.� 	Develop and maintain relationships with Aegon partners to create global collaborationopportunities in development and management of products.� 	Set performance standards, review performance, provide feedback and recommend salary compensation plans that are competitive in the marketplace.� 	Manage direct reports and others to ensure cooperation and consistencies across various departments/groups.� 	Enforce accountability for performance and resolve conflicts timely. Ensure that the responsibilities, authorities and accountability of all subordinates are defined and understood.� 	Foster collaboration within the local and global organizationQualifications:� 	Bachelor�s degree in Finance, Marketing, Business or related field required� 	Minimum 10 years� experience successfully leading product initiatives at the senior level.� 	Superior management skills; ability to influence and engage direct and indirect reports and peers; ability to drive complex situations and projects to desired outcome� 	Thorough knowledge and understanding of the Institutional asset management business and marketplace across the key product segments of fixed income and real estate.� 	Detailed understanding of processes associated regulatory requirements in captive and third party asset management businesses� 	Strong analytical skills� 	Ability to interact with people of all levels and diverse personalities/cultures� 	Excellent communication, presentation, interpersonal and organizational skills� 	Ability to set goals and objectives for self and others while monitoring activities and results� 	Solid knowledge of strategic planning� 	Flexible, collaborative and proactive; a leader who can positively and productively impact bothstrategic and tactical initiativesEqual Employment Opportunity:AEGON USA, Realty Advisors, LLC., is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate against any applicant or employee because of age, religion, sex, gender identity, genetic information, race, color, national origin, pregnancy, sexual orientation, marital status, participation in the uniformed services (e.g. U.S. Armed Forces, National Guard), physical or mental disability, or any other status protected by federal, state, or local equal employment opportunities laws.Applicants with physical or mental disabilities may be entitled to a form of reasonable accommodation under the Americans with Disabilities Act and certain state and local laws. A reasonable accommodation is a change in the way things are normally done which will insure equal employment opportunitywithout imposing undue hardship on AEGON USA, Realty Advisors, LLC. Please inform the Human Resources department if you need assistance completing any forms, or to otherwise participate in the application process. https://www.transamerica.com/individual/about-us/careers/


