Management Board


    
    
    The eleven members of Aegon’s Management Board work alongside the Executive Board, and help oversee operational issues and the implementation of Aegon’s strategy.
    

Members are drawn from Aegon's business and country units, and have both  regional and global responsibilities. This ensures that Aegon is  managed as an integrated international business. While the Executive  Board remains Aegon's sole statutory executive body, the Management  Board provides vital support and expertise in pursuit of the company's  strategic objectives.
Management Board Documentation >
AGM Documentation Archive >


























Alexander R. Wynaendts
(1960, Nationality: Dutch)
CEO and Chairman of the Executive and Management Boards of Aegon N.V.
In 1997, Mr. Wynaendts joined Aegon as Senior Vice President for Group Business Development. In 2007 he was appointed as Aegon's Chief Operating Officer, and in 2008 CEO. Read more >






